# Property-team data model

Canonical access and **per-user profile** are **property-team based**. There is no separate user profile entity.

## Hierarchy

- **Property** = `propertiesTYG` row
- **Team member / ACL / profile** = one object in `propertiesTYG.metadata.property_team[]` per user on that property
- **Auth identity** = Supabase `auth.users` only (login/session). Profile fields (name, title, phone, alias, card accent, etc.) live on the matching `property_team` member — not a parallel table

## Do

- Store and update display/profile fields on the `property_team` member record for the active property
- Prefer columns or metadata on `propertiesTYG` (and existing domain tables like sessions/leads) over new entity graphs
- Keep interoperability with legacy shapes already keyed by property + team member

## Do not (without explicit user approval)

- Use, extend, or depend on `user_profiles` as the source of truth for profile data (treat as legacy to migrate off)
- Create new tables for companies, org memberships, agents, or junction tables that parallel `property_team`
- Treat `company_memberships` (or similar invalidated legacy org tables) as authoritative for access or profile
- Introduce a separate “agent entity” or global profile table when the agent is already a `property_team` member

If a feature seems to need a new table outside this hierarchy, **stop and ask** before writing migrations.
